  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Membership Not sure whether Quantum is for you? Try us for one week FREE! There is n o long-term commitment or obligation, sign up when you’re ready! Monthly dues Monthly dues include access to unlimited classes, and Quantum offers over 35 classes per week for all ages. Attending 2-3 classes per week is recommended for successful results.  Monthly dues for all ages are in addition to a sliding-scale yearly membership fee. If you are in a position to offer more than the rate marked below, every dollar will go toward providing martial arts classes that are accessible for all. Adults (age 13+) monthly dues are $225 per month. Teens age 13-17 are invited to try our Adult Program at $200 per month. Kids & Teens (ages 6–14), monthly dues for the first student are $200 per month. Quarks (ages 4–5), monthly dues are $175 per month. Family discounts: Families training together will receive a discount of $15 off each family members’ dues. Yearly membership In addition to monthly dues, our annual membership levels are: $40 – Currently enrolled college student, discounted rate $60 – Minimum rate for adult Quantum Student $80 – Quantum Family (covers unlimited family members training in the kids or adults programs) $125 – Quantum Benefactor $250 – Quantum Supporter $500 – Quantum Patron $1000 – Quantum Angel Scholarships and Donations As a not-for-profit organization, Quantum is a place where valuable training and life-skills are available to all. As such, we offer a sliding-scale tuition and a scholarship program to families and adults who qualify for assistance . Sliding scale tuition is established through conversation on the honor system. We do not require proof of need via paystubs or ask for families’ yearly income. You don’t have to be currently training in order to support Quantum with a yearly membership. All instructors are volunteers and we survive on membership, donations, grants, and support from our community. Alumni, friends and family members, and patrons of the martial arts are encouraged to support our school with an honorary membership. No donation amount is too little or too large, and your gift is tax-deductible. Donations are accepted via PayPal , or contact Master Evans to arrange your donation today! Questions on membership? Please contact us . Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
